docs.abstract: Introduced 10 years ago, the app has slowly become a popular way to keep track of friends. But it comes with considerable privacy concerns.
docs.snippet: Introduced 10 years ago, the app has slowly become a popular way to keep track of friends. But it comes with considerable privacy concerns.
docs.lead_paragraph: In July, Shay Pierre opened Apple’s location-sharing app Find My and noticed a friend at an unfamiliar apartment building in Fort Lauderdale, Fla.

headline.main: How the Find My App Became an Accidental Friendship Fixture

docs.abstract: John Lasseter was toppled five years ago by allegations about his workplace behavior. He’s back with an animated film and a studio that could be Pixar 2.0.
docs.snippet: John Lasseter was toppled five years ago by allegations about his workplace behavior. He’s back with an animated film and a studio that could be Pixar 2.0.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — The most Pixar movie of the summer is not from Pixar. It’s from Apple TV+ and the lightning-rod filmmaker-executive who turned Pixar into a superpower: John Lasseter.

headline.main: Pixar’s Ousted Founder Returns With Apple and ‘Luck’
headline.print_headline: Apple TV+ To Air Latest By Visionary Pixar Ousted

docs.abstract: A sweeping bill that would enact the strongest restrictions on Big Tech companies in the United States has been stalled in the Senate.
docs.snippet: A sweeping bill that would enact the strongest restrictions on Big Tech companies in the United States has been stalled in the Senate.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Critics of the country’s largest tech companies branded the last few months “Hot Antitrust Summer” because they hoped that Congress would vote on new regulations for Amazon, Apple, Google and Facebook.

headline.main: Clock Running Out on Antitrust Bill Targeting Big Tech
headline.print_headline: Clock Is Running Out on an Antitrust Bill Targeting Big Tech Companies

byline.original: By David McCabe and Stephanie Lai

docs.abstract: Simple steps can make your smartphone, computer and TV work better for you.
docs.snippet: Simple steps can make your smartphone, computer and TV work better for you.
docs.lead_paragraph: Many default settings buried deep inside our technology make us share superfluous amounts of data with tech companies. In my last column, I went over how to shut those off.

headline.main: Change These Default Settings and Be Happier With Your Tech
headline.print_headline: Simple Steps To Fine-Tune Your Gadgets

docs.abstract: An airport worker in Florida was charged with two counts of grand theft after a tracking device aided a sheriff’s investigation.
docs.snippet: An airport worker in Florida was charged with two counts of grand theft after a tracking device aided a sheriff’s investigation.
docs.lead_paragraph: A traveler who put a tracking device in her bag helped sheriff’s deputies in Florida identify an airport worker who was accused of stealing more than $16,000 in goods from passengers’ luggage, the authorities said.

headline.main: She Had an AirTag in Her Lost Luggage. It Led Police to a Baggage Handler’s Home.
headline.print_headline: After Luggage Went Missing, AirTag Helped Find the Thief
